Amper, Abertis, Popular, Ferrovial, Iberdrola: Iberian Preview

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s   a n d   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-02-23T07:39:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/amper-banco-popular-ferrovial-iberdrola-iberian-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index  fell 1 percent to 10,701.90.
Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index  gained 0.2 percent to 7,869.55.  Spanish stocks:    Abertis Infraestructuras SA  (ABE SM): The Spanish company
said it may group its five units into two companies, Abertis
Infrastructuras and Saba Infraestructuras, according to a
regulatory filing. Abertis may group its highways,
telecommunications and airport divisions into Abertis
Infrastructuras and its parking and logistics parks into Saba.
The stock slipped 0.1 percent to 14.41 euros.    Amper SA  (AMP SM): The Spanish defense contractor won a
contract worth more than 90 million euros from the United Arab
Emirates. The shares rose 3.6 percent to 3.77 euros.  Banco Popular Espanol SA (POP SM), Bankinter SA (BKT SM):
Standard & Poor’s Ratings Services cut its credit ratings on
Banco Popular and gave Bankinter a negative outlook as it
predicted a “difficult” year for Spanish lenders. Popular
shares lost 1.1 percent to 4.37 euros. Bankinter shares gained
0.5 percent to 4.78 euros.    Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA  (BBVA SM) has started to
liquidate its BBVA Propiedad real estate fund two and a half
years after it was frozen, El Confidencial reported, citing
unidentified people with knowledge of the matter. BBVA has
valued the fund at 1.4 billion euros, a discount of 20 percent
to the valuation it had in October 2008, it added. The shares
fell 1.6 percent to 8.91 euros.  Ferrovial SA (FER SM): The Spanish construction company is
scheduled to report earnings before the market opens. The shares
gained 1.8 percent to 8.70 euros.  Iberdrola SA (IBE SM): Spain’s biggest power company will
propose to its next shareholders meeting a 2010 gross dividend
of 3 euro cents per share. The Spanish company will also propose
a bonus share issue as part of its dividend program. The shares
lost 1.4 percent to 6.22 euros.    Iberdrola Renovables SA  (IBR SM): The world’s biggest
producer of renewable energy is scheduled to report earnings
after the market closes. The shares lost 0.2 percent to 2.67
euros.    Jazztel Plc  (JAZ SM): The Spanish broadband operator is
scheduled to report earnings. The shares lost 0.8 percent to
3.97 euros.    Solaria Energia y Medio Ambiente SA  (SLR SM): The Spanish
solar-cell manufacturer said full-year profit jumped to 6.5
million euros from 2.5 million euros a year earlier. Sales
climbed 81 percent to 161.3 million euros. The shares dropped
2.1 percent to 1.61 euros.  Portuguese stocks:    Zon Multimedia Servicos de Telecomunicacoes e Multimedia
SGPS SA  (ZON PL): Portugal´s biggest pay-television company said
profit in the fourth quarter rose 26 percent. Net income rose to
3.9 million euros from a restated 3.1 million euros a year
earlier, Lisbon-based Zon said in regulatory filing. The shares
rose 1.3 percent to 3.80 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Ben Sills in Madrid at   bsills@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:  David Merritt  at 
 dmerritt1@bloomberg.net  